        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 20 at 5:35PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 535 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Berrien Springs, or 7 miles southeast of Fair Plain, moving north at
15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Berrien Springs, Coloma, Sodus, Eau Claire, Spinks Corners, and
Millburg.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 196 between mile markers 0 and 2.
Interstate 94 in Michigan between mile markers 34 and 38.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
